==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lictor
<hw>Lic"tor</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧k"t⟦ocr⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L.]</ety> <fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld> <def>An officer who bore an ax
and fasces or rods, as ensigns of his office. His duty was to attend the
chief magistrates when they appeared in public, to clear the way, and
cause due respect to be paid to them, also to apprehend and punish
criminals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Lictors</qex> and rods, the ensigns of their power.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lid</ent>⟦br⟧
